<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36220a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36220a">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36220a"> 220(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ instrument / the ap. / aaronic / transfiguration</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Mormonism.]</font> I have previously alluded to <cite>The Prophecies of Joseph Smith and Their Fulfillment</cite> by Elder Morris &hellip; It is <font color="green">[Morris&apos;s]</font> abiding conviction that &ldquo;we are now in the Dispensation of the Fullness of Times.&rdquo; This is the Dispensation referred to by the Apostle Peter and subscribed to by Senator Smoot. The <mark>instrument</mark> which gave us this Dispensation, which &hellip; will culminate in the millennial reign of Christ, was none other than Joseph Smith. As expressed by Morris &hellip; John the Baptist, &ldquo;who held the keys of the Lesser or <mark>Aaronic</mark> Priesthood in the earlier dispensation, appeared in his resurrected state and ordained Joseph Smith and Oliver Cowdery.&rdquo; Later, the presiding three of the first Twelve Apostles, to wit, Peter, James and John, ordained these men to &ldquo;the holy apostleship, conferring upon them the higher or Melchizideck Priesthood&hellip;&rdquo; It must be emphasized that the powers thus conferred upon Joseph Smith of Palmyra, New York, were the same which Jesus, Moses and Elias conferred upon Peter, James, and John during the mystical experience on the mount of <mark>Transfiguration</mark>. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 374</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
